---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
import HttpMethod from '../../components/docs/HttpMethod.astro'
---

<DocsLayout title="Introduction" section="getting-started" page="index">
    <h1>DocExtract API</h1>
    <p class="lede">
        Turn PDFs and images into structured JSON with a single HTTP call.
    </p>

    <p>
        The DocExtract API is a small REST surface for running document
        extraction jobs. Send a file plus the id of an extraction template,
        get a JSON object that matches your schema. Authentication uses an
        API token issued from your dashboard.
    </p>

    <h2>Base URL</h2>
    <p>All requests target a single base URL, scoped per environment:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Production: <code>https://api.doc-extraction.com</code></li>
        <li>Development: <code>https://api-develop.doc-extraction.com</code></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Endpoints at a glance</h2>
    <div class="not-prose my-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
        <table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
            <thead class="bg-gray-50 text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500">
                <tr>
                    <th class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Method</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Path</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Auth</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Purpose</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 text-[13px]">
                <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-2.5"><HttpMethod method="POST" /></td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono text-gray-900">
                        <a href="/docs/endpoints/extract" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">
                            /v1/extract
                        </a>
                    </td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-gray-600">Token</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-gray-700">
                        Upload a file and start an extraction.
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-2.5"><HttpMethod method="GET" /></td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono text-gray-900">
                        <a href="/docs/endpoints/get-extraction" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">
                            /v1/extractions/:id
                        </a>
                    </td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-gray-600">Token</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-gray-700">
                        Poll an extraction's status and parsed result.
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-2.5"><HttpMethod method="GET" /></td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono text-gray-900">
                        <a href="/docs/endpoints/list-products" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">
                            /products
                        </a>
                    </td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-gray-600">Public</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-gray-700">List the catalogue with prices.</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>

    <h2>Conventions</h2>
    <p>
        Every JSON response shares the same envelope, whether the call succeeds
        or fails:
    </p>

    <pre class="not-prose my-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-4 text-[13px] text-gray-900"><code>{`// Success
{ "data": <T>, "error": false }

// Failure
{ "data": null, "error": true, "message": "Human-readable explanation" }`}</code></pre>

    <p>
        HTTP status codes carry the same semantics as the REST world expects:
        2xx for success, 4xx for caller mistakes, 5xx for ours. Quota issues
        come back as <strong>402</strong>, not 429 — see <a href="/docs/errors">Errors &amp; rate limits</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Next steps</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <a href="/docs/quickstart">Quickstart</a> — make your first
            extraction in under a minute.
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="/docs/authentication">Authentication</a> — how API tokens
            work and how to keep them safe.
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="/docs/endpoints/extract">POST /v1/extract</a> — the
            endpoint you'll use most often.
        </li>
    </ul>
</DocsLayout>
